business\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3151}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 3157, \"to\": 3165}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The USA would not allow it.\", \"from\": 3177, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3181, \"end\": 3184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.142810086758503e-17, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Exactly why remains partially mysterious.\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Surely, post-1991, it was in the interest of U.S. military contractors to maintain their Cold War revenue streams.\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3293, \"end\": 3306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9204038205523964e-19, \"text\": \"U.S. military\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the interest\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3289}, {\"ngram\": \"their Cold War revenue streams\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3361}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To do that, a foreign hobgoblin had to be invoked - and perhaps China was not the best candidate, since it had begun manufacturing everything on sale in the Walmart - so Russia, with practically no export economy besides energy (which is considerable), was cast in that role.\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3427, \"end\": 3432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8806970130910958e-13, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3533, \"end\": 3539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a foreign hobgoblin\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3394}, {\"ngram\": \"the best candidate\", \"from\": 3441, \"to\": 3459}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3504}, {\"ngram\": \"sale\", \"from\": 3508, \"to\": 3512}, {\"ngram\": \"the Walmart\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3527}, {\"ngram\": \"practically no export economy\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3575}, {\"ngram\": \"energy\", \"from\": 3584, \"to\": 3590}, {\"ngram\": \"that role\", \"from\": 3628, \"to\": 3637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the politicians, too, surely liked creaming off their share of that military-industrial revenue stream, so they went along policywise, with figures like John McCain and Lindsey Graham leading the charge.\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3797, \"end\": 3808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McCain\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.8871785946179326e-12, \"text\": \"John McCain\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McCain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McCain\"}, {\"begin\": 3813, \"end\": 3827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Graham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lindsey Graham\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Graham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Graham\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the politicians\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3659}, {\"ngram\": \"their share\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3703}, {\"ngram\": \"that military-industrial revenue stream\", \"from\": 3707, \"to\": 3746}, {\"ngram\": \"policywise\", \"from\": 3767, \"to\": 3777}, {\"ngram\": \"figures\", \"from\": 3784, \"to\": 3791}, {\"ngram\": \"the charge\", \"from\": 3836, \"to\": 3846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the U.S. intel blob and State Department had darker motives, driven by an animus that has slowly revealed itself to be insane - just as the Democratic Party has turned obviously insane, adopting a playbook that could have been written by Franz Kafka.\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 4103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3993, \"end\": 4009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9994310418913448, \"rank\": 0.0005692820058613208, \"text\": \"Democratic Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 4091, \"end\": 4102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Kafka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Franz Kafka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Kafka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Kafka\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S. intel blob and State Department\", \"from\": 3853, \"to\": 3893}, {\"ngram\": \"darker motives\", \"from\": 3898, \"to\": 3912}, {\"ngram\": \"an animus\", \"from\": 3924, \"to\": 3933}, {\"ngram\": \"a playbook\", \"from\": 4048, \"to\": 4058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being likewise insane, the intel blob and the neocons at State harbored an unappeasable hatred toward Russia that, since the Soviet collapse, allowed no accommodation and gelled into a naked avarice for seizing the resources of Russia with a long-term plan to subvert the Russian state, break it up the way they broke up Serbia in the 1990s and direct a corporate looting operation of Russia's oil and mineral riches.\", \"from\": 4105, \"to\": 4522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4207, \"end\": 4213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4230, \"end\": 4245, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dissolution_of_the_Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Soviet collapse\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dissolution_of_the_Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dissolution_of_the_Soviet_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 4333, \"end\": 4339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4377, \"end\": 4384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999866799530905, \"rank\": 1.3196079211421151e-05, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 4426, \"end\": 4432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9961835311163084, \"rank\": 0.003829197273119747, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 4490, \"end\": 4496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the intel blob\", \"from\": 4128, \"to\": 4142}, {\"ngram\": \"the neocons\", \"from\": 4147, \"to\": 4158}, {\"ngram\": \"State\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4167}, {\"ngram\": \"an unappeasable hatred\", \"from\": 4177, \"to\": 4199}, {\"ngram\": \"no accommodation\", \"from\": 4255, \"to\": 4271}, {\"ngram\": \"a naked avarice\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4303}, {\"ngram\": \"the resources\", \"from\": 4316, \"to\": 4329}, {\"ngram\": \"a long-term plan\", \"from\": 4345, \"to\": 4361}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 4404, \"to\": 4411}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1990s\", \"from\": 4436, \"to\": 4445}, {\"ngram\": \"a corporate looting operation\", \"from\": 4457, \"to\": 4486}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ukraine was the doorway they had to go through to get that done.\", \"from\": 4524, \"to\": 4588, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4524, \"end\": 4531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0855217448621279e-22, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the doorway\", \"from\": 4536, \"to\": 4547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And so the blob and State neocons overthrew democratically elected Viktor Yanukovych in 2014, and installed Poroshenko followed by Zelenskyy.\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4657, \"end\": 4674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Yanukovych\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Viktor Yanukovych\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Yanukovych\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Yanukovych\"}, {\"begin\": 4698, \"end\": 4708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Petro_Poroshenko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Poroshenko\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Petro_Poroshenko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Petro_Poroshenko\"}, {\"begin\": 4721, \"end\": 4730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Zelenskyy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zelenskyy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Zelenskyy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Zelenskyy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the blob and State neocons\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4623}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Veep \\\"Joe Biden\\\" was given the Ukraine \\\"portfolio,\\\" making him a sort of viceroy, and he took full advantage, plopping his son Hunter on the board of Burisma, the huge Ukrainian natgas company that American oil and gas companies drooled over.\", \"from\": 4733, \"to\": 4975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4739, \"end\": 4742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.9999473962901086, \"rank\": 5.190370138698976e-05, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 4743, \"end\": 4748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3172708827662394e-22, \"text\": \"Biden\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\"}, {\"begin\": 4764, \"end\": 4771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0855217448621279e-22, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 4860, \"end\": 4866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.617086947403375e-54, \"text\": \"Hunter\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.or